The Hawks say the five men and two women were caught with mortar bombs worth approximately R3.7 million. JOHANNESBURG - Seven suspects who were arrested while allegedly selling military explosives in Mpumalanga this week have appeared in the Tonga magistrates court.The Hawks say the five men and two women were caught with mortar bombs worth approximately R3.7 million. Spokersperson Dineo Sekgotodi says preliminary investigations suggest the explosives may have been smuggled from neighbouring countries. The suspects appeared before Tonga Magistrates Court and they were granted bail of R1,500 each. The case is postponed to 21 July 2017 for further investigation. (Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)